# grapher_ineq_parabola_smoke.numos — Phase 10D. Plot y>x^2: the region ABOVE the
# parabola. lhs="y" rhs="x^2" so G=y-x^2 and the solution is G>0. Proves an
# inequality with y on the left and a function on the right shades correctly.
# Warning-only (no golden); NOT CI-gated.
log "ineq parabola: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
# Type "y>x^2"
key y
key gt
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 60
# Zoom in 2x so the vertex region is large.
key zoom
key zoom
wait 120
screenshot out/grapher_ineq_parabola_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "ineq parabola: y>x^2 shaded"
